This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it proposes a new method for modeling Q-values and policies over continuous spaces using neural networks. Additionally, the paper draws inspiration from recent success in sequence-to-sequence models for structured prediction problems, which is a common area of research in machine learning. 

The paper may also belong to the sub-category of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as it deals with developing policies for continuous control problems, which is a common area of research in AI. 

Furthermore, the paper may belong to the sub-category of cs.RO (Robotics) as it applies the proposed method to off-policy (Q-learning) methods for several continuous control tasks, which is a common area of research in robotics. 

The paper may also belong to the sub-category of cs.CV (Computer Vision) as it uses neural networks to model complex functions over high dimensional spaces, which is a common area of research in computer vision. 

Finally, the paper may belong to the sub-category of cs.SY (Systems and Control) as it deals with developing policies for continuous control problems, which is a common area of research in systems and control.
